284
00:16:32,697 --> 00:16:34,616
We're twinning!

285
00:16:36,361 --> 00:16:37,528
So cute!

286
00:16:37,904 --> 00:16:40,073
So are we both rockstars now?

287
00:16:40,949 --> 00:16:41,908
You know Alys,

288
00:16:41,908 --> 00:16:43,279
you don't look like a rockstar.

289
00:16:43,952 --> 00:16:45,161
You look sweet.

290
00:16:45,161 --> 00:16:47,163
You can't pull off boots like that one.

291
00:16:48,331 --> 00:16:50,333
Kei, that’s a bit much.

292
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:53,724
I just wanted to look cool like you.

293
00:16:55,004 --> 00:16:57,458
Just be yourself, Alys.

294
00:16:58,549 --> 00:17:00,176
I am being myself.

295
00:17:02,261 --> 00:17:03,388
How's Sheen?

296
00:17:04,430 --> 00:17:05,556
Sheen?

297
00:17:06,664 --> 00:17:07,790
He's fine, I guess.

298
00:17:08,351 --> 00:17:10,228
I heard he's here on vacation.

299
00:17:13,564 --> 00:17:14,774
Oh...

300
00:17:14,774 --> 00:17:15,608
Really?

301
00:17:16,401 --> 00:17:17,235
Mhm.

302
00:17:17,235 --> 00:17:18,528
That's good to hear.

303
00:17:19,362 --> 00:17:20,279
So?

304
00:17:20,822 --> 00:17:22,532
I'll get these, okay?

305
00:17:22,532 --> 00:17:23,366
My treat!

306
00:17:26,411 --> 00:17:27,495
Hi!

307
00:17:27,495 --> 00:17:29,872
Can I get new stocks for these?

308
00:17:29,872 --> 00:17:31,624
Thank you!

309
00:17:41,259 --> 00:17:42,635
Where'd she go?

310
00:17:42,635 --> 00:17:44,303
Where is Kei?

311
00:17:47,974 --> 00:17:48,975
Oh...

312
00:17:48,975 --> 00:17:50,560
Where did Kei go?

313
00:17:50,893 --> 00:17:52,937
I don't have her phone number.

314
00:17:54,272 --> 00:17:57,650
Why do I keep forgetting to ask
people's numbers?

315
00:17:58,401 --> 00:17:59,902
I remember Drake.

316
00:18:00,236 --> 00:18:03,823
I've known him for almost a
year before I got his number.

317
00:18:05,867 --> 00:18:07,201
Where is Kei?

318
00:18:07,201 --> 00:18:09,454
She didn’t leave me, right?

319
00:18:19,756 --> 00:18:21,748
My legs are killing me.

320
00:18:22,258 --> 00:18:23,301
What's with Kei?

321
00:18:23,301 --> 00:18:25,261
She really just left me here.

322
00:18:25,261 --> 00:18:26,721
I've gone through the entire mall

323
00:18:26,721 --> 00:18:28,181
and I couldn't find her.

324
00:18:28,514 --> 00:18:29,522
It hurts.

325
00:18:36,522 --> 00:18:39,442
Tripp must be doing the same thing.

326
00:18:40,234 --> 00:18:43,154
He loves taking pictures.

327
00:18:45,740 --> 00:18:48,451
What would I do if I ran into him?

328
00:18:48,743 --> 00:18:50,661
That Talkative Tofer said

329
00:18:51,664 --> 00:18:54,092
that he'd be going to NYCU too.

330
00:19:03,966 --> 00:19:05,301
Tripp!

331
00:19:06,345 --> 00:19:07,889
Shouldn't she be in Manila?

332
00:19:10,959 --> 00:19:11,960
Hi?

333
00:19:18,856 --> 00:19:20,100
I forgot to buy something.

334
00:19:30,217 --> 00:19:31,344
Wrong move.

335
00:19:32,453 --> 00:19:33,579
I can do this.

336
00:19:37,875 --> 00:19:39,252
I didn't know you were here, Tripp!

337
00:19:39,252 --> 00:19:40,253
Hey!

338
00:19:40,253 --> 00:19:40,878
Hey!

339
00:19:40,878 --> 00:19:41,678
You, too!

340
00:19:43,214 --> 00:19:44,107
Uh...

341
00:19:44,924 --> 00:19:46,259
Are you with Drake?

342
00:19:46,801 --> 00:19:47,468
No!

343
00:19:47,468 --> 00:19:49,345
Uh, I'm just here to study.

344
00:19:49,345 --> 00:19:50,217
What about you?

345
00:19:50,346 --> 00:19:50,967
Oh!

346
00:19:51,848 --> 00:19:52,849
Uh, me too!

347
00:19:53,307 --> 00:19:54,934
I go to NYCU.

348
00:19:55,143 --> 00:19:56,514
Oh, I go to NYCU, too.

349
00:19:56,815 --> 00:19:57,880
You too?

350
00:20:03,359 --> 00:20:04,944
Okay, then.

351
00:20:06,571 --> 00:20:07,488
Tripp!

352
00:20:07,488 --> 00:20:08,281
Wait!

353
00:20:08,990 --> 00:20:09,967
Tripp, wait!

354
00:20:14,036 --> 00:20:14,453
Aish!

355
00:20:14,495 --> 00:20:15,246
Ahh!

356
00:20:15,788 --> 00:20:16,779
Hey, what happened?

357
00:20:16,998 --> 00:20:17,779
What happened?

358
00:20:17,957 --> 00:20:21,252
My leg cramped up.
I've been walking all day.

359
00:20:22,378 --> 00:20:23,443
Uh...

360
00:20:23,713 --> 00:20:24,630
Can you walk?

361
00:20:25,798 --> 00:20:27,049
My leg really hurts.

362
00:20:29,404 --> 00:20:30,344
Gosh.

363
00:20:31,262 --> 00:20:32,180
Uhm...

364
00:20:33,639 --> 00:20:34,557
Zy?

365
00:20:35,308 --> 00:20:36,287
Piggyback ride?

366
00:20:39,629 --> 00:20:42,549
If I let you carry me,
will we be best friends again?

367
00:20:43,941 --> 00:20:45,401
When did we become best friends?

368
00:20:46,277 --> 00:20:47,862
Come on, Tripp.

369
00:20:58,331 --> 00:20:59,303
Hop on.

370
00:21:09,759 --> 00:21:12,303
We're best friends again, okay?

371
00:21:16,390 --> 00:21:19,185
So, what's your degree program, Tripp?

372
00:21:20,102 --> 00:21:22,438
Dad still wants Business Ad for me.

373
00:21:22,730 --> 00:21:24,690
Oh! We're in the same program.

374
00:21:24,690 --> 00:21:26,651
I major in Advertising.

375
00:21:27,709 --> 00:21:28,669
Really?

376
00:21:28,694 --> 00:21:30,264
I'm so happy to see you.

377
00:21:30,458 --> 00:21:32,710
But I'm still trying
to move on from you.

378
00:21:32,907 --> 00:21:34,242
How am I supposed to do that?

379
00:21:34,408 --> 00:21:35,576
Should we compare schedules?

380
00:21:35,576 --> 00:21:37,745
Maybe we have classes in common.

381
00:21:38,579 --> 00:21:39,561
Sure.

382
00:21:44,919 --> 00:21:46,170
Drake?

383
00:21:47,630 --> 00:21:48,422
What?

384
00:21:48,422 --> 00:21:49,507
Drake?

385
00:21:50,229 --> 00:21:51,939
Shaira's downstairs.
She's looking for you.

386
00:21:51,964 --> 00:21:53,674
Tell her, I'll go down in a bit.

387
00:21:54,345 --> 00:21:56,055
Can't she just come up?

388
00:21:56,555 --> 00:21:57,723
Dad,

389
00:21:57,723 --> 00:21:59,016
I have a girlfriend.

390
00:21:59,016 --> 00:22:00,309
Kindly bear that in mind.

391
00:22:00,810 --> 00:22:01,991
I'll go down to see her.

392
00:22:02,103 --> 00:22:03,145
Okay, okay.

393
00:22:25,302 --> 00:22:26,343
Drake!

394
00:22:30,381 --> 00:22:31,561
What?

395
00:22:31,931 --> 00:22:33,224
I've decided

396
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:36,178
to leave the country.

397
00:22:36,512 --> 00:22:38,764
I just spoke to Alys last night.
And...

398
00:22:40,516 --> 00:22:42,643
She's so nice.

399
00:22:43,561 --> 00:22:45,604
Why does she have to be so nice?

400
00:22:46,230 --> 00:22:47,857
Don't know.

401
00:22:47,857 --> 00:22:48,649
She's too nice.

402
00:22:48,649 --> 00:22:49,817
It's kinda annoying.

403
00:22:50,484 --> 00:22:52,069
I wish to see her being bad.

404
00:22:52,653 --> 00:22:54,405
I want to see her
in a whole new light.

405
00:22:55,740 --> 00:22:56,741
Huh?

406
00:22:56,741 --> 00:22:58,117
Why?

407
00:23:00,578 --> 00:23:01,954
Well, anyway...

408
00:23:02,204 --> 00:23:03,748
Because of that,

409
00:23:03,748 --> 00:23:06,208
I've decided to stay
with my aunt in London.

410
00:23:06,625 --> 00:23:09,061
I'll stop studying for a year and...

411
00:23:09,539 --> 00:23:10,991
I'll see where that takes me.

412
00:23:12,757 --> 00:23:13,758
Are you sure?

413
00:23:20,014 --> 00:23:22,141
I'll miss you, hubby.

414
00:23:24,018 --> 00:23:25,436
Sure, Shaira.

415
00:23:25,436 --> 00:23:26,395
Call me.

416
00:23:27,897 --> 00:23:28,939
No!

417
00:23:28,939 --> 00:23:32,693
I'm not gonna call you
until I'm completely over you.

418
00:23:33,235 --> 00:23:34,570
Don't forget me, okay?

419
00:23:35,905 --> 00:23:38,240
Of course, silly.
When's your flight?

420
00:23:39,617 --> 00:23:41,535
Sometime next week.

421
00:23:41,535 --> 00:23:43,371
How about you?
When are you leaving for the States?

422
00:23:43,495 --> 00:23:44,579
This afternoon.

423
00:23:45,081 --> 00:23:46,457
This afternoon?

424
00:23:54,048 --> 00:23:55,383
I'll miss you, Shaira.

425
00:23:56,967 --> 00:23:57,860
For real?

426
00:23:57,885 --> 00:23:58,882
For sure.

427
00:24:00,679 --> 00:24:01,764
Hubby!

428
00:24:07,645 --> 00:24:09,968
Bee, show Sheen on the phone.

429
00:24:10,231 --> 00:24:11,273
What's up?

430
00:24:11,982 --> 00:24:13,109
Listen, Sheen.

431
00:24:13,109 --> 00:24:14,568
You're my best friend.

432
00:24:14,568 --> 00:24:16,153
Take care of my girlfriend!

433
00:24:16,737 --> 00:24:18,406
Don't be dramatic!

434
00:24:18,406 --> 00:24:20,116
I'll be gone for two weeks!

435
00:24:20,116 --> 00:24:23,369
You're briefing CB like
I'm going away for a year.

436
00:24:23,786 --> 00:24:26,163
And besides, this is your fault!

437
00:24:26,163 --> 00:24:27,832
You chose summer classes

438
00:24:27,832 --> 00:24:29,959
over a vacation in New York!

439
00:24:30,251 --> 00:24:31,252
Sorry about that, Bee!

440
00:24:32,263 --> 00:24:33,585
Alright then.

441
00:24:34,046 --> 00:24:35,631
I have to charge my phone.

442
00:24:35,840 --> 00:24:36,590
Alright, Bee.

443
00:24:36,590 --> 00:24:37,716
Call you later.

444
00:24:38,217 --> 00:24:41,085
Don't bother!
We're taking off soon.

445
00:24:41,262 --> 00:24:43,305
There won't be cell service in the air.

446
00:24:43,305 --> 00:24:45,304
And I plan to sleep on the plane.

447
00:24:45,516 --> 00:24:48,644
Well then, I'll see you in your dreams.

448
00:24:49,562 --> 00:24:52,280
Oh, Kent, you're so corny.

449
00:24:52,314 --> 00:24:53,691
But, okay.

450
00:24:53,691 --> 00:24:55,151
See you in my dreams.

451
00:24:55,651 --> 00:24:56,777
Bye!

452
00:24:59,864 --> 00:25:01,115
So, how are you and Kei?

453
00:25:01,991 --> 00:25:04,686
Bestie told me that they were roommates!

454
00:25:05,119 --> 00:25:06,370
Imagine that!

455
00:25:06,704 --> 00:25:09,415
Out of all the people in New York,

456
00:25:09,633 --> 00:25:10,968
she's with Kei Chui!

457
00:25:12,168 --> 00:25:13,461
That's okay.

458
00:25:14,003 --> 00:25:14,944
Really?

459
00:25:15,421 --> 00:25:16,827
That's okay?

460
00:25:17,631 --> 00:25:18,799
We talk.

461
00:25:19,216 --> 00:25:20,217
Mostly, in chat.

462
00:25:20,468 --> 00:25:21,374
Okay?

463
00:25:22,011 --> 00:25:23,095
So...

464
00:25:23,721 --> 00:25:24,757
You're still together?

465
00:25:26,640 --> 00:25:27,808
Will you stop it?

466
00:25:27,808 --> 00:25:29,185
We are friends.

467
00:25:29,185 --> 00:25:30,102
Period.

468
00:25:31,562 --> 00:25:32,646
Besides...

469
00:25:33,063 --> 00:25:34,148
I like someone else.

470
00:25:42,656 --> 00:25:43,991
Knock it off, CB!

471
00:25:44,617 --> 00:25:46,285
I have my Honey.

472
00:25:46,827 --> 00:25:48,496
And I'm his Bee, right?

473
00:25:48,746 --> 00:25:51,290
The Bee to his Honey!

474
00:25:51,832 --> 00:25:52,750
Okay?!

475
00:25:52,875 --> 00:25:54,168
Ladies and gentlemen,

476
00:25:54,502 --> 00:25:56,129
- Okay.
- this is the boarding announcement...

477
00:25:56,337 --> 00:25:57,671
Okay! Great!

478
00:25:57,755 --> 00:26:00,716
...to New York’s John F. Kennedy
International Airport.

479
00:26:01,258 --> 00:26:03,511
- We are now inviting passengers...
- Let’s go!

480
00:26:03,511 --> 00:26:04,535
Hey!

481
00:26:04,946 --> 00:26:06,449
Aya, you left your luggage!

482
00:26:07,714 --> 00:26:08,643
Aya!

483
00:26:09,725 --> 00:26:10,824
Aya, wait!

484
00:26:13,562 --> 00:26:14,897
For Monday class,

485
00:26:14,897 --> 00:26:17,316
most Advertising freshie students

486
00:26:17,316 --> 00:26:19,276
have morning classes
around 9:00 AM.

487
00:26:19,568 --> 00:26:20,486
For example,

488
00:26:20,486 --> 00:26:22,530
your course in
Advertising Principles,

489
00:26:22,530 --> 00:26:26,116
lecture-based and usually
lasts about 75 minutes.

490
00:26:27,326 --> 00:26:30,204
Isn't that a bit early for
such a boring class?

491
00:26:30,539 --> 00:26:31,430
Well,

492
00:26:31,455 --> 00:26:33,165
after that, around 11:00 AM,

493
00:26:33,165 --> 00:26:36,043
you've got Graphic Design for Advertising.

494
00:26:36,043 --> 00:26:38,045
Those are more hands-on.

495
00:26:38,045 --> 00:26:41,674
Expect brainstorming sessions,
Photoshop work,

496
00:26:41,674 --> 00:26:43,133
and small group projects .

497
00:26:43,592 --> 00:26:48,222
Great! I think I'll be more interested
in designing than those lectures.

498
00:26:48,847 --> 00:26:50,808
By the way, are we allowed
to have food in class?

499
00:26:51,350 --> 00:26:52,935
Eating inside the room is not allowed.

500
00:26:52,935 --> 00:26:54,603
You can have lunch at 1:00 PM.

501
00:26:54,603 --> 00:26:57,106
And you'll end the day
with Brand Management.

502
00:26:57,106 --> 00:26:58,440
But that'll be at 3:00 PM.

503
00:26:58,580 --> 00:26:59,748
You'll have time to chill until then.

504
00:27:00,469 --> 00:27:02,236
Are we clear now, Perez?

505
00:27:04,822 --> 00:27:05,573
Alright, then.

506
00:27:05,573 --> 00:27:07,074
I'll be in the next building.

507
00:27:07,074 --> 00:27:07,967
I still have a class.

508
00:27:07,992 --> 00:27:09,201
Alright! Thanks, Kei!

509
00:27:09,201 --> 00:27:10,411
Very much appreciated!

510
00:27:10,411 --> 00:27:11,399
Okay.

511
00:27:12,329 --> 00:27:14,665
I kept nodding along but
the truth is,

512
00:27:15,082 --> 00:27:17,251
I still don't know what to do.

513
00:27:17,668 --> 00:27:18,711
It's so early!

514
00:27:19,044 --> 00:27:20,879
And I don't even know anyone here.

515
00:27:21,422 --> 00:27:23,799
What if I fall asleep in class?

516
00:27:24,216 --> 00:27:27,094
Good luck, Alys!

517
00:27:29,805 --> 00:27:32,516
Well, if it isn't my lucky day!

518
00:27:32,516 --> 00:27:33,684
Tripp!

519
00:27:35,232 --> 00:27:36,691
Which class are you going to?

520
00:27:37,062 --> 00:27:39,148
Advertising Principles 101.

521
00:27:39,857 --> 00:27:41,066
In fairness,

522
00:27:41,066 --> 00:27:42,943
Tripp's looking handsome today.

523
00:27:43,736 --> 00:27:44,653
Room 2A?

524
00:27:45,821 --> 00:27:47,740
We're classmates!

525
00:27:47,906 --> 00:27:48,549
Really?

526
00:27:48,574 --> 00:27:50,409
That’s right!
So, let's go together?

527
00:27:50,576 --> 00:27:51,387
Let's go!

528
00:27:56,248 --> 00:27:57,708
"No classes today."

529
00:27:57,708 --> 00:28:00,169
"Next meeting, submit a
paper on Advertising Schemes."

530
00:28:00,336 --> 00:28:02,296
"12, Times New Roman.
Double-spaced. "

531
00:28:02,296 --> 00:28:03,547
"Minimum of five pages."

532
00:28:03,547 --> 00:28:05,549
Minimum of five pages?!

533
00:28:05,549 --> 00:28:07,009
Are they serious?!

534
00:28:07,009 --> 00:28:09,386
The next meeting is in two days!

535
00:28:10,220 --> 00:28:12,139
What did I get myself into?

536
00:28:12,139 --> 00:28:14,808
I'm not sure if I'm in school or purgatory.

537
00:28:15,434 --> 00:28:17,102
Well, let's get started!

538
00:28:17,645 --> 00:28:18,604
Did you bring your laptop?

539
00:28:19,438 --> 00:28:20,939
I left it in my locker.

540
00:28:20,939 --> 00:28:21,815
Are you sure?

541
00:28:22,608 --> 00:28:23,484
Come on!

542
00:28:25,819 --> 00:28:26,695
Let’s go, Zy!

543
00:28:27,363 --> 00:28:28,238
Okay, fine.

544
00:28:28,781 --> 00:28:29,657
You can do this. Let’s go.

545
00:28:30,282 --> 00:28:31,408
Fine, I'm going!

546
00:28:33,147 --> 00:28:35,983
There’s no class, but there’s an essay.
It’s crazy.

547
00:28:36,830 --> 00:28:38,540
Wait for me!

548
00:28:45,506 --> 00:28:47,341
I've written three pages already.

549
00:28:49,093 --> 00:28:50,260
Three pages?!

550
00:28:51,637 --> 00:28:53,972
It's barely been thirty minutes!

551
00:28:54,848 --> 00:28:55,933
That's not fair!

552
00:28:56,475 --> 00:28:57,726
Why? How's yours?

553
00:29:02,648 --> 00:29:03,578
Show me.

554
00:29:09,446 --> 00:29:10,507
My god, Alys!

555
00:29:10,739 --> 00:29:12,866
We've been here the whole time,
and that's all you've got?!

556
00:29:15,494 --> 00:29:16,704
Well then, I'm sorry!

557
00:29:16,704 --> 00:29:18,038
I'm not the brightest.

558
00:29:18,038 --> 00:29:19,373
You know that!

559
00:29:20,874 --> 00:29:21,929
And also,

560
00:29:22,084 --> 00:29:23,919
my brain processes things pretty slowly.

561
00:29:25,754 --> 00:29:26,255
Give it to me.

562
00:29:26,255 --> 00:29:27,210
I'll do it.

563
00:29:27,423 --> 00:29:27,715
Let me.

564
00:29:27,715 --> 00:29:29,758
No, Tripp! It’s embarassing!

565
00:29:33,137 --> 00:29:34,638
Alright, you do it.

566
00:29:34,638 --> 00:29:36,223
I'll let you take care of that.

567
00:29:36,223 --> 00:29:38,726
Not one word is coming
out of my brain right now.

568
00:29:40,978 --> 00:29:42,146
My god, Alys.

569
00:29:42,146 --> 00:29:43,522
How did you even pass the exams?

570
00:29:44,064 --> 00:29:45,983
Why are you such a meanie?

571
00:29:46,692 --> 00:29:47,943
No, seriously!

572
00:29:47,943 --> 00:29:50,612
How are you going to pass
if you don’t take this seriously?

573
00:29:51,822 --> 00:29:53,685
I am sorry, dad!

574
00:29:53,907 --> 00:29:57,077
It's because I'm always on
a video call with Drake so...

575
00:29:57,077 --> 00:29:57,911
that’s why.

576
00:29:57,911 --> 00:30:00,247
I never get a chance
to review in advance.

577
00:30:13,943 --> 00:30:15,095
Tripp?

578
00:30:16,638 --> 00:30:18,140
Thank you for this.

579
00:30:19,308 --> 00:30:20,309
Don't mention it.

580
00:30:21,650 --> 00:30:23,277
I'll make your presentation, too.

581
00:30:23,896 --> 00:30:24,855
Seriously?!

582
00:30:24,855 --> 00:30:26,648
Wouldn't that be
taking advantage of you?

583
00:30:27,399 --> 00:30:28,942
Sound good?

584
00:30:29,526 --> 00:30:30,527
Thank you!

585
00:30:36,799 --> 00:30:37,633
Zy?

586
00:30:38,761 --> 00:30:40,732
Don't do video calls
with Drake just yet, okay?

587
00:30:41,038 --> 00:30:42,206
Focus on your acads.

588
00:30:42,790 --> 00:30:44,500
Yes, boss!

589
00:30:54,843 --> 00:30:56,220
Dear lord.

590
00:30:56,857 --> 00:30:57,846
It's Tofer.

591
00:30:57,846 --> 00:30:59,264
He's looking for me again.

592
00:31:00,724 --> 00:31:01,600
Speaking of Tofer,

593
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:03,811
as in Christofer Ann Palma.

594
00:31:03,811 --> 00:31:05,646
He's really is a lot to take, isn't he?

595
00:31:07,439 --> 00:31:08,599
He told me, you two met.

596
00:31:08,899 --> 00:31:10,025
He's such a troublemaker, right?

597
00:31:10,025 --> 00:31:13,212
Exactly! Seriously, he's driving me crazy!

598
00:31:13,237 --> 00:31:15,113
You know, I can tolerate Aya.

599
00:31:15,113 --> 00:31:16,443
With him, it's impossible!

600
00:31:17,324 --> 00:31:19,201
I don’t even know how I’m tolerating him.

601
00:31:19,201 --> 00:31:20,327
He's like...

602
00:31:20,327 --> 00:31:21,787
He's like a grown-up kid.

603
00:31:21,787 --> 00:31:24,122
He didn’t even grow taller.

604
00:31:24,414 --> 00:31:25,654
Now, you're the meanie.

605
00:31:27,376 --> 00:31:28,252
Poor kid.

606
00:31:28,252 --> 00:31:29,753
Sshh, let’s keep it a secret.

607
00:31:29,778 --> 00:31:30,825
Oh gosh.

608
00:31:31,046 --> 00:31:31,911
Poor kid.

609
00:31:33,090 --> 00:31:34,800
By the way, I'll walk you home, okay?

610
00:31:36,051 --> 00:31:37,135
Okay!

611
00:31:56,488 --> 00:31:57,823
Where were you?

612
00:31:57,948 --> 00:31:59,950
You startled me.

613
00:32:00,409 --> 00:32:02,494
Uh, I went to class earlier.

614
00:32:02,744 --> 00:32:04,705
Okay.
Someone's waiting for you.

615
00:32:06,248 --> 00:32:07,207
Who?

616
00:32:08,375 --> 00:32:09,543
Okay.

617
00:32:18,640 --> 00:32:20,099
Drake!

618
00:32:22,222 --> 00:32:23,682
Hi, girlfriend!

619
00:32:24,892 --> 00:32:26,351
O to the M to the G!

620
00:32:26,351 --> 00:32:28,103
Is that really you, Drake?!

621
00:32:28,838 --> 00:32:29,964
Weirdo.

622
00:32:34,359 --> 00:32:35,402
I missed you!

623
00:32:39,990 --> 00:32:41,575
You look different, Alys.

624
00:32:42,117 --> 00:32:43,138
Wow!

625
00:32:43,702 --> 00:32:44,786
You like?

626
00:33:01,727 --> 00:33:02,978
Hey, Tripp!

627
00:33:03,472 --> 00:33:04,723
What’s your problem now?

628
00:33:08,018 --> 00:33:09,728
What’s the news this time?

629
00:33:09,937 --> 00:33:11,188
Who got knocked up this time?

630
00:33:11,325 --> 00:33:12,869
Drake's in town.

631
00:33:15,317 --> 00:33:16,285
Drake?

632
00:33:17,110 --> 00:33:17,903
Mhm!

633
00:33:17,903 --> 00:33:19,154
He's here!

634
00:33:21,490 --> 00:33:22,491
Oh!

635
00:33:23,124 --> 00:33:25,090
Alys is here so
Drake's here, too.

636
00:33:25,619 --> 00:33:26,828
Makes sense.

637
00:33:27,162 --> 00:33:29,623
Why are you still surprised?
She’s your cousin’s girlfriend —

638
00:33:29,957 --> 00:33:31,208
the one you love.

639
00:33:31,683 --> 00:33:33,226
I told Uncle Steve,

640
00:33:33,251 --> 00:33:34,586
to let Drake stay with us.

641
00:33:34,978 --> 00:33:36,730
But get this...

642
00:33:36,755 --> 00:33:38,340
Drake turned it down!

643
00:33:38,340 --> 00:33:39,636
He checked in to a hotel!

644
00:33:41,134 --> 00:33:42,636
Why do you think Drake
doesn’t like us?

645
00:33:42,636 --> 00:33:43,597
That’s so mean.

646
00:33:44,918 --> 00:33:46,348
You know why he doesn’t like to be here?

647
00:33:46,765 --> 00:33:47,824
Hmm?

648
00:33:47,849 --> 00:33:48,976
Because you're here.

649
00:33:48,976 --> 00:33:49,351
Huh?

650
00:33:49,351 --> 00:33:50,894
You know he's allergic to you.

651
00:33:51,269 --> 00:33:52,329
That's not true!

652
00:33:52,354 --> 00:33:53,939
Drake is just mean!

653
00:33:54,231 --> 00:33:55,524
Okay, listen...

654
00:33:56,024 --> 00:33:58,777
Alys is nice. Drake is bad.

655
00:33:59,111 --> 00:34:00,420
They’re not a good match, man!

656
00:34:00,445 --> 00:34:02,948
You and Alys are a good match, you know.

657
00:34:03,198 --> 00:34:04,241
If you think about it!

658
00:34:04,241 --> 00:34:05,742
I'm Tripplys for life!
You know that!

659
00:34:12,599 --> 00:34:13,266
You’re so noisy!

660
00:34:13,291 --> 00:34:14,710
Go away! I have things to do!

661
00:34:15,085 --> 00:34:16,589
- I can't focus.
- Fine, but...

662
00:34:16,614 --> 00:34:18,115
Team Tripplys for life!

663
00:34:59,421 --> 00:35:00,504
Shoot.

664
00:35:33,594 --> 00:35:35,930
Gosh, Marco is brilliant!

665
00:35:36,458 --> 00:35:38,223
No wonder he passed.

666
00:35:39,002 --> 00:35:41,379
How are we in the same class?

667
00:35:41,379 --> 00:35:44,466
What if Mom paid off
the proctors to let me in?

668
00:35:50,180 --> 00:35:51,431
What are you doing?

669
00:35:52,808 --> 00:35:54,476
Nothing. Nothing.

670
00:35:57,646 --> 00:35:59,147
Does your head feel better?

671
00:36:03,110 --> 00:36:04,611
I missed you, Noob.

672
00:36:05,403 --> 00:36:06,655
Let's eat outside.

673
00:36:07,364 --> 00:36:08,615
Okay!

674
00:36:16,790 --> 00:36:17,833
Drake.

675
00:36:17,833 --> 00:36:19,334
Would you just stay at my dorm,

676
00:36:19,334 --> 00:36:21,211
instead of the hotel, please?

677
00:36:21,211 --> 00:36:24,214
Are you suggesting pre-marital sex, Alys?

678
00:36:25,298 --> 00:36:27,300
Hey! How rude!

679
00:36:27,416 --> 00:36:28,584
Of course not!

680
00:36:29,177 --> 00:36:30,679
I just want to sleep beside you

681
00:36:30,679 --> 00:36:32,055
because I missed you!

682
00:36:32,055 --> 00:36:33,348
Unbelievable.

683
00:36:33,348 --> 00:36:34,349
Stupid.

684
00:36:34,349 --> 00:36:36,268
It's an all female dorm, remember?

685
00:36:37,811 --> 00:36:39,062
You’re right.

686
00:36:39,062 --> 00:36:40,188
Sorry!

687
00:36:41,606 --> 00:36:42,732
By the way,

688
00:36:44,985 --> 00:36:46,496
I'm on speaking terms with Dad.

689
00:36:47,161 --> 00:36:49,830
My boyfriend’s doing very good!

690
00:36:49,948 --> 00:36:51,366
Improving!

691
00:36:51,366 --> 00:36:52,207
And...

692
00:36:52,588 --> 00:36:53,593
And?

693
00:36:53,618 --> 00:36:55,078
I'm telling you this

694
00:36:55,745 --> 00:36:57,581
because I don't want to
keep things from you

695
00:36:57,998 --> 00:37:01,209
since I hate secrets.

696
00:37:01,209 --> 00:37:04,176
Me too!
I don't like secrets either.

697
00:37:05,130 --> 00:37:07,841
So? What are our plans tomorrow?

698
00:37:08,758 --> 00:37:10,802
Don't you have your classes tomorrow?

699
00:37:12,095 --> 00:37:13,121
Uh, no!

700
00:37:13,409 --> 00:37:15,223
I don't have classes.

701
00:37:15,432 --> 00:37:16,933
I'm free tomorrow!

702
00:37:17,684 --> 00:37:18,810
Okay.

703
00:37:18,810 --> 00:37:19,942
See you tomorrow.

704
00:37:20,187 --> 00:37:21,153
Okay!

705
00:37:21,938 --> 00:37:23,098
See you tomorrow!

706
00:37:37,996 --> 00:37:39,539
Good morning, everyone!

707
00:37:39,956 --> 00:37:42,567
Welcome to Advertising Principles 101!

708
00:37:42,834 --> 00:37:44,252
I'm Professor Scott.

709
00:37:44,252 --> 00:37:45,837
And this course will
be your foundation

710
00:37:45,837 --> 00:37:48,882
in understanding how
advertising really works,

711
00:37:48,882 --> 00:37:51,927
beyond just the catchy slogans
and the pretty posters.

712
00:37:52,840 --> 00:37:54,092
Zyril...

713
00:37:54,694 --> 00:37:56,070
Where are you?

714
00:37:56,806 --> 00:37:58,433
I thought we’re okay.

715
00:37:59,309 --> 00:38:01,478
Why are you being so harsh?

716
00:38:02,520 --> 00:38:03,496
There!

717
00:38:03,855 --> 00:38:05,398
- We're going there?
- Mhm.

718
00:38:08,151 --> 00:38:12,447
Now, let's discuss the first principles
of Advertising.

719
00:38:14,790 --> 00:38:16,083
She really didn’t show up.

720
00:38:17,285 --> 00:38:18,411
Unbelievable.

721
00:38:20,080 --> 00:38:21,957
My baby is so grumpy.

722
00:38:23,583 --> 00:38:24,793
I missed you.

723
00:38:24,793 --> 00:38:25,903
Really?

724
00:38:25,961 --> 00:38:26,753
Mhm.

725
00:38:26,753 --> 00:38:28,838
Thank you for coming here!

726
00:38:34,513 --> 00:38:35,847
Where are you, Zy?

727
00:38:40,850 --> 00:38:42,435
So, where are we going next?

728
00:38:47,065 --> 00:38:48,775
She really didn't show up.

729
00:38:55,657 --> 00:38:59,244
Okay! So, that will be
your homework today.

730
00:38:59,869 --> 00:39:00,787
Class dismissed.

731
00:39:00,787 --> 00:39:01,705
Oh!

732
00:39:02,551 --> 00:39:03,957
For anyone who was absent today,

733
00:39:03,957 --> 00:39:06,793
please let them know that
I require a five page essay

734
00:39:06,793 --> 00:39:09,296
detailing the reason for their absence.

735
00:39:09,754 --> 00:39:11,543
Don't come to my class without it.

736
00:39:12,808 --> 00:39:14,895
- Thank you, sir.
- Thank you, sir.

737
00:39:18,513 --> 00:39:19,556
Way to go, Alys.

738
00:39:20,334 --> 00:39:22,252
The class only just started

739
00:39:22,712 --> 00:39:24,964
and you're already being a headache.

740
00:39:36,281 --> 00:39:38,283
So, where do you want to go next?

741
00:39:38,283 --> 00:39:39,576
I'm free today!

742
00:39:42,570 --> 00:39:46,433
Please bring the following requirements:
Sketchbook or visual journal.

743
00:39:46,458 --> 00:39:47,418
Alys!

744
00:40:06,978 --> 00:40:08,188
That's hot!

745
00:40:08,188 --> 00:40:09,397
Oh!

746
00:40:19,032 --> 00:40:20,283
Are you having fun?

747
00:40:30,919 --> 00:40:31,795
Reminder to everyone.

748
00:40:31,795 --> 00:40:33,505
Only 3 absences are allowed.

749
00:40:33,505 --> 00:40:36,841
Those who already have 3 absences
must attend class today,

750
00:40:36,841 --> 00:40:39,177
or will need to drop
this course altogether.

751
00:40:39,177 --> 00:40:41,721
Alys Perez, please meet me in my office.

752
00:40:43,973 --> 00:40:46,434
Drake, I have a class.

753
00:40:46,434 --> 00:40:48,228
I totally forgot I had one.

754
00:40:49,428 --> 00:40:50,778
Bad girlfriend.

755
00:40:51,439 --> 00:40:52,732
You lied to me?

756
00:40:53,608 --> 00:40:57,112
I'm sorry.
I just wanted to bond with you today.

757
00:40:59,322 --> 00:41:00,528
Alys...

758
00:41:01,116 --> 00:41:03,284
Why do you always act like I'll be gone?

759
00:41:03,971 --> 00:41:06,140
I'm not going anywhere.
I'm here beside you.

760
00:41:06,579 --> 00:41:07,705
Holding your hand.

761
00:41:09,040 --> 00:41:10,750
I won't go anywhere, Alys.

762
00:41:11,527 --> 00:41:12,695
I love you, Drake.

763
00:41:13,128 --> 00:41:14,963
My love for you is crazy.

764
00:41:15,422 --> 00:41:17,215
And I don't like crazy.

765
00:41:17,746 --> 00:41:20,457
Being in love with you makes
me do crazy things.

766
00:41:21,261 --> 00:41:22,554
Makes me go to different heights,

767
00:41:22,554 --> 00:41:24,681
and to be honest,
it's scaring the shit out of me.

768
00:41:24,806 --> 00:41:26,933
But I love being in love with you, Alys.

769
00:41:27,350 --> 00:41:28,977
And so long as I live,

770
00:41:29,144 --> 00:41:31,574
I'll continue loving you to
the moon and back, Alys.

771
00:41:32,060 --> 00:41:33,478
To the moon and back.

772
00:41:34,197 --> 00:41:35,426
See you tomorrow.

773
00:41:35,628 --> 00:41:37,338
Go to your classes, okay?

774
00:41:37,527 --> 00:41:38,489
Okay!

775
00:41:39,904 --> 00:41:41,823
Bye! See you tomorrow!

776
00:41:58,256 --> 00:42:01,134
Oh, for heaven's sake, Ms. Perez!

777
00:42:01,386 --> 00:42:02,971
If you’re not determined to learn here,

778
00:42:02,996 --> 00:42:06,229
there is still time for you to
drop out!

779
00:42:06,996 --> 00:42:08,861
Stop wasting my time.

780
00:42:10,893 --> 00:42:14,480
I'm so sorry, Mr. Scott.
I'll do better.

781
00:42:15,398 --> 00:42:16,733
You better.

782
00:42:32,499 --> 00:42:33,791
Drake!

783
00:42:35,533 --> 00:42:37,420
What are you doing here?

784
00:42:37,587 --> 00:42:39,756
Did you miss me already?

785
00:42:46,262 --> 00:42:47,263
Hey!

786
00:42:47,796 --> 00:42:49,840
You’re still mesmerized by how pretty I am.

787
00:42:50,225 --> 00:42:51,059
Oh...

788
00:42:51,559 --> 00:42:53,937
I still have classes
at the other building.

789
00:42:53,962 --> 00:42:56,506
I thought you said
you'd see me tomorrow?

790
00:42:57,148 --> 00:42:58,650
Go to class, Alys.

791
00:42:58,983 --> 00:43:01,653
Please, get your life together.

792
00:43:03,947 --> 00:43:05,573
What did you say, Drake?

793
00:43:05,657 --> 00:43:07,534
I said you look different.

794
00:43:08,993 --> 00:43:10,912
I'll take that as a compliment.

795
00:43:12,121 --> 00:43:13,456
I’ve a question.

796
00:43:16,834 --> 00:43:18,878
Is it really true that you’re
dating my cousin?

797
00:43:52,954 --> 00:43:54,260
See you tomorrow.

798
00:43:54,285 --> 00:43:55,995
Go to your classes, okay?

799
00:43:56,165 --> 00:43:56,924
Okay!

800
00:43:58,876 --> 00:44:00,044
See you tomorrow!

801
00:44:03,548 --> 00:44:04,643
So, that's why.

802
00:44:07,719 --> 00:44:08,678
That's great, Alys.

803
00:44:09,483 --> 00:44:11,735
Put your boyfriend first
before your studies.

804
00:44:27,787 --> 00:44:29,596
So that's why Zy was absent.

805
00:44:37,811 --> 00:44:40,063
Did you know her
professor humiliated her?

806
00:44:43,090 --> 00:44:44,197
Oh well.

807
00:44:45,329 --> 00:44:46,479
That’s because she’s always absent.

808
00:44:48,718 --> 00:44:51,596
She's the only one who
can't complete one week.

809
00:44:53,389 --> 00:44:54,479
You know why?

810
00:44:56,370 --> 00:44:59,123
She always stays up late
waiting for your call or text.

811
00:45:02,899 --> 00:45:04,736
Alys will fail, Drake!

812
00:45:08,446 --> 00:45:10,900
Clearly, you don't know her!

813
00:45:13,117 --> 00:45:14,243
So that's it, then?

814
00:45:14,952 --> 00:45:16,537
You're just going to let her fail?

815
00:45:19,636 --> 00:45:21,096
Why am I not surprised?

816
00:45:21,190 --> 00:45:22,024
You haven't changed!

817
00:45:22,049 --> 00:45:24,080
What the fuck you want, Tripp?!

818
00:45:24,796 --> 00:45:27,033
Why am I the only one seeing
that kind of behavior?

819
00:45:28,892 --> 00:45:31,460
People think you're so perfect.

820
00:45:31,928 --> 00:45:33,846
"Drake Palma, he’s so mature."

821
00:45:35,807 --> 00:45:38,017
When the truth is,
you're inconsiderate!

822
00:45:38,017 --> 00:45:40,687
If I’m inconsiderate,
I would ask her to come home.

823
00:45:41,979 --> 00:45:43,106
Fine!

824
00:45:43,611 --> 00:45:44,791
Why not?

825
00:45:45,525 --> 00:45:46,818
She's failing anyway!

826
00:45:46,818 --> 00:45:48,111
She won't fail!

827
00:45:49,404 --> 00:45:50,446
Do you know that?

828
00:45:51,114 --> 00:45:52,532
Are you sure?

829
00:45:56,536 --> 00:45:58,079
What do you even know?

830
00:46:00,112 --> 00:46:02,197
Because I can already see it very clearly.

831
00:46:03,618 --> 00:46:04,947
One text from you?

832
00:46:05,420 --> 00:46:07,046
And she'll drop everything she's doing.

833
00:46:08,381 --> 00:46:10,007
And when you don't text her?

834
00:46:10,942 --> 00:46:12,277
She doesn’t do anything.

835
00:46:12,427 --> 00:46:13,928
She’s overthinking.

836
00:46:13,928 --> 00:46:15,430
She's worried.

837
00:46:17,699 --> 00:46:19,200
She is here, Drake.

838
00:46:19,225 --> 00:46:21,811
But she's not making an effort to stay
because of you!

839
00:46:25,523 --> 00:46:26,899
So please,

840
00:46:28,466 --> 00:46:29,842
just take Alys home.

841
00:46:34,111 --> 00:46:36,322
Don't you see how
she looks down on herself?

842
00:46:38,369 --> 00:46:39,704
And I can't blame her!

843
00:46:40,788 --> 00:46:43,666
When people call dumb or stupid...

844
00:46:45,101 --> 00:46:46,695
I don't want her to get hurt again.

845
00:46:47,920 --> 00:46:50,047
I don't want to see her fail.

846
00:46:51,007 --> 00:46:53,801
I don't want to see that
disappointed look on her face!

847
00:46:56,087 --> 00:46:57,421
So, please!

848
00:46:58,723 --> 00:47:00,308
Take her home!

849
00:47:02,060 --> 00:47:03,645
Before she breaks.

850
00:47:05,737 --> 00:47:07,322
Given what's happening now,

851
00:47:09,317 --> 00:47:10,902
she's already headed that way.

852
00:47:13,036 --> 00:47:14,621
It's because of you.

853
00:47:15,782 --> 00:47:16,949
You're bad for her, Drake.

854
00:47:19,202 --> 00:47:21,859
You're pulling Alys down
and you fucking know it!

855
00:47:32,647 --> 00:47:34,232
If you’re not determined to learn here,

856
00:47:34,257 --> 00:47:37,385
there is still time for you to
drop out!

857
00:47:38,304 --> 00:47:40,723
Stop wasting my time!

858
00:47:42,225 --> 00:47:45,770
I'm so sorry, Mr. Scott. I’ll do better.

859
00:47:46,604 --> 00:47:47,890
You better.

860
00:47:57,412 --> 00:47:58,454
Drake!

861
00:48:00,519 --> 00:48:02,270
What are you doing here?

862
00:48:02,411 --> 00:48:04,997
Did you miss me already?

863
00:48:06,040 --> 00:48:08,140
Am I really pulling you down, Alys?

864
00:48:18,766 --> 00:48:21,671
On the next episode of Dating Alys Perez.

865
00:48:21,696 --> 00:48:22,613
Are you leaving?

866
00:48:23,891 --> 00:48:24,914
Drake!

867
00:48:25,499 --> 00:48:27,293
Did I do something wrong?

868
00:48:27,666 --> 00:48:29,751
Stop wasting your time on me.

869
00:48:30,032 --> 00:48:31,617
Stop thinking about me.

870
00:48:31,642 --> 00:48:32,768
I've made up my mind.

871
00:48:32,793 --> 00:48:34,295
Let's call it quits.

872
00:48:34,720 --> 00:48:37,055
Try and get in that cab, Drake!

873
00:48:38,075 --> 00:48:40,202
I’ll forget you even if it’s hard, Drake!

874
00:48:43,767 --> 00:48:48,480
You will regret this, Drake Palma!

875
00:48:49,557 --> 00:48:52,143
He doesn’t love me anymore.

876
00:48:53,287 --> 00:48:54,621
Okay, Zy. It's ready.

877
00:48:55,756 --> 00:48:57,091
It’s so basic to make —

878
00:48:58,217 --> 00:49:00,928
Someone told me
that since I let you go,

879
00:49:01,144 --> 00:49:03,188
I should be the one taking you back.

880
00:49:03,741 --> 00:49:05,075
Tripp is my boyfriend.

881
00:49:05,475 --> 00:49:06,642
What's wrong with you?
